		<h2><Strong>Emma Bunton</Strong></h2>
		<h5>'Baby Spice'</h5>
    <p> Born Emma Lee Bunton in London, England on January 21, 1976. She was nicknamed 'Baby Spice.' She is a singer, songwriter, television judge, radio presenter and actress. After her time with the Spice Girls, she began working as a radio presenter from 2013-2018. She has also released a few solo albums. She has been dating former singer and current chef Jade Jones since 2004. The couple have two sons together, Tate and Beau Lee Jones.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="Geri Halliwell" class="bg-light">
