      <h2><strong>Geri Halliwell</strong></h2>
      <h5>'Ginger Spice'</h5>
      <p> Geri Halliwell was born Geraldine Estelle Horner, on August 6, 1972 in Hertfordshire England. She was nicknamed 'Ginger Spice.' She is a singerm songwriter, philanthropist, author, and actress. She was the reason of The Spice Girls being so associated with "girl power." She left the group in 1998 to pursue a solo career. She has also released solo albums. She has been married to Christian Horner, principal of Red Bull Racing since 2015. She has two children, Bluebell Madonna Halliwell and Montague George Hector Horner.</p>

    </section>

